<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870429-0108 </DOCNO><HL> Bayly Corp. Will Spin OffIts Aspen Leaf Retail Unit</HL><DD> 04/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BAYL OTFEDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bayly Corp. said it will spin off its Aspen Leaf Inc. retail unit into a separate, publicly held company.    Bayly, a clothing maker, said the action will result in a nonrecurring charge of about 55 cents a share in the second quarter. Bayly is 51%-owned by OTF Equities Inc., a Detroit-based holding company.    Bayly said it will distribute as a dividend all its shares in Aspen Leaf to Bayly stock of record June 15. Bayly holders will receive one Aspen Leaf common share and a warrant to purchase one additional share at a specified price for each Bayly share held. Bayly said neither it nor Aspen Leaf will receive any proceeds from the distribution. </TEXT></DOC>